 &lt;p&gt;⭐️⭐️⭐️&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&#34;https://leetcode.com/problems/sequential-digits/?envType=daily-question&amp;amp;envId=2024-02-02&#34;&gt;&lt;ins class=&#34;dot&#34;&gt;題目敘述&lt;/ins&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An integer has &lt;em&gt;sequential digits&lt;/em&gt; if and only if each digit in the number is one more than the previous digit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return a &lt;strong&gt;sorted&lt;/strong&gt; list of all the integers in the range  &lt;code&gt;[low, high]&lt;/code&gt;  inclusive that have sequential digits.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-1&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-1&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 1&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; low = 100, high = 300&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [123,234]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;example-2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#example-2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Example 2&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input:&lt;/strong&gt; low = 1000, high = 13000&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt; [1234,2345,3456,4567,5678,6789,12345]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
